		<Backstory>Faxia was once the favored daughter of one of the Fifth Patriarch's nobles.  As it became rapidly apparent what was happening in the kingdom, her father tried to rally support to stage a coup.  As a backup plan in case of his failure, he paid for a protective ward from a foreign magician to protect Faxia's spirit from the spells of the Skeleton King.  Unfortunately for the noble, his plan came to naught and he was converted like the rest of the ruling caste. Unfortunately for Faxia, the ward also failed to prevent her own conversion to an undead state.  It did, however, have an effect, in that she retained her free will and memories of her former life, as well as some lingering minor protections.  Embittered by her fate, and not wanting to test whether the ward would last, she left the kingdom.

When she left, she soon discovered that she was unwelcome in most other lands.  Eventually she was taken in by a broad-minded shadow, who also happened to be an assassin.  Faxia apprenticed herself to the assassin, figuring that if she couldn't live her own life, she could at least earn a living taking lives from others.  In time she proved to have quite the natural talent; also, she learned, looking like death itself isn't really a social disadvantage in the assassins' trade.</Backstory>

